---
import sunriseTheme from '../../assets/sunriseTheme.svg';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<div id="digital-literacy-container">
  <img id="background" src={sunriseTheme.src} alt="Sunrise Theme Background" fetchpriority="high" />
  <main>
    <section id="project-details">
      <h1>Digital Literacy Workshops</h1>
      <p>
        Our Digital Literacy Workshops are designed to empower individuals with the essential digital skills needed to thrive in today's tech-driven world. Through hands-on sessions, participants will learn practical skills that they can apply immediately in their personal and professional lives.
      </p>

      <h2>Workshop Goals</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email Management:</strong> Learn how to use email effectively, including organizing, sending professional messages, and avoiding common pitfalls like spam or phishing.</li>
        <li><strong>Safe Browsing:</strong> Understand how to navigate the internet securely, recognize potential threats, and protect personal data.</li>
        <li><strong>Productivity Tools:</strong> Get hands-on experience with tools like Google Workspace or Microsoft Office to streamline tasks and improve efficiency.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What You Will Gain</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Confidence in using digital tools for everyday tasks.</li>
        <li>Practical skills to enhance personal and professional communication.</li>
        <li>Knowledge to protect yourself and others from online threats.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Join This Project?</h2>
      <p>
        Digital literacy is essential in today's world, yet many people lack access to quality training. By joining this project, you'll help bridge the digital divide while gaining valuable experience in teaching and community engagement.
      </p>

      <h2>Volunteer Opportunities</h2>
      <p>
        Volunteers can participate as trainers, content creators, or coordinators. Whether you have technical expertise or organizational skills, there's a role for you in making this project successful.
      </p>

      <a href="/community-projects" class="button">Back to Community Projects</a>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</div>

<style>
  #background {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    z-index: -1;
    filter: blur(50px);
  }

  #digital-literacy-container {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    height: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #FFF3E0, #FFE0B2);
    color: #E65100;
  }

  main {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  #project-details {
    padding: 16px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(255, 87, 34, 0.1);
    border: 2px solid #FF5722;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    text-align: left;
  }

  #project-details h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  #project-details p, #project-details ul {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  #project-details h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  #project-details ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    color: white;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #FF9800, #FF5722);
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }

  .button:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #E65100, #FF5722);
  }

  footer {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #F57C00;
  }
</style>
